      "content": "it feels less like a \"process\" and more like a dead end. i look at him and i just feel like i'm waiting for something that's never coming back. i'm just tired of the heaviness. sometimes i think the only way to actually stop feeling this way is to just... stop. to not have to fight the silence anymore. does that sound crazy? like, is it even fair to keep going when everything that made life worth it is just gone?",
